<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="53" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">600.939/239: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-11T19:00:00-04:00">August 11, 1938—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>281. Your 520, August 8, 3 p.m., via Tientsin.<note n="57" xml:id="d53fn57">Not printed.</note> In the light of Tientsin’s 154,
                            August 10, 3 p.m.,<note n="57" xml:id="d53fn1">Not printed.</note> the
                            Department suggests that in your discretion you defer further action for
                            a few days pending a clarification of the situation. If in your opinion
                            action should then still be considered desirable, you may use your
                            discretion with reference to the contents of the proposed <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>